R. H. GREEN, A. M. Green and J. B. Green, Doing Business as Green & Green, v. LUDFORD FRUIT PRODUCTS, Incorporated. No. 10066. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Feb. 26, 1942. Brezina & Buckingham and Joseph F. Westall, all of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellants. Rupert B. Turnbull, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before DENMAN, MATHEWS, and STEPHENS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On stipulation of counsel for respective parties, and good cause therefor appearing, ordered appeal herein, D.C., 39 F.Supp. 985, dismissed, that a decree be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
